  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`SafeMath#div` doesn't perform any checks because division cannot overflow. It currently simply returns the result of the `/` operator. However, it may be considered \"unsafe\" the fact that integer division truncates the result, and this may be unexpected to users who think they are doing a safe operation, as implied by the name of the library.\r\n\r\nI think we should address this, and consider either removing `div` from `SafeMath`, or adding checks to `SafeMath#div` ensure there was no truncation. The latter doesn't make much sense to me.",
